TaxaMask Notice

TaxaMask is a taxonomy-oriented mask annotation, literature figure extraction,
and multimodal dataset production workbench.

Project origin:

TaxaMask was originally developed for ant taxonomy research. The internal Python
package name `AntSleap` is retained for runtime compatibility and as a tribute
to SLEAP, the animal pose-estimation project that inspired the original
development direction. The external project and user-facing name is TaxaMask.

Research use and citation:

If TaxaMask contributes to a publication, preprint, dataset, benchmark, or
public research output, please cite the repository release and DOI when
available. See CITATION.cff for the current preferred citation metadata.

